# tooling-justfile-pixi-ecosystem-wrapping ‚Äî History

## v4.0.0 (2026-04-05)

**Changed by:** Odysseus meta-repo delegation task ‚Äî 4-submodule myrmidon swarm with submodule-first workflow
**Verification:** verified-local

### What changed
- Added **Template C: Meta-Repo Delegation** with the `cd <submodule-path> && just <recipe>` pattern and section header convention
- Added **Submodule-First Workflow** section: 2-wave myrmidon swarm (Wave 1: submodule PRs in parallel, Wave 2: Odysseus delegation + pin updates)
- Updated "When to Use" to include meta-repo delegation trigger
- Updated frontmatter description to mention `just <prefix>-<recipe>` delegation
- Added 3 new failed attempts: NATS pipeline overengineering, concurrent writes to Odysseus justfile, single consolidated PR across repos
- Added "Meta-Repo Delegation Parameters" table (4 submodules, 2 waves, ~3 min total)
- Added "Delegation Recipe Naming Convention" table for all submodules
- Added Odysseus row to "Verified On" table
- Added tags: `meta-repo`, `submodule`, `myrmidon-swarm`, `delegation`

### Why
Template A and B covered individual repo justfiles (pixi delegation). The meta-repo delegation
pattern (Odysseus `just fleet-build` ‚Üí `cd infrastructure/AchaeanFleet && just build`) is a
distinct use case with its own pitfalls: submodule-first ordering, wave serialization to avoid
shared-file conflicts, and the overengineering trap of containerized pipelines. These learnings
belong here since they extend the justfile ecosystem convention to the top-level meta-repo.

